commit.message:
Release 1.3.10

- access to unknown IFD fields
- support TIFF floats and doubles

Handle bad GPS records

GPS latitude/longitude are encoded using rationals.  Some cameras encode
missing information with 0/0 values for unknown rational data.  This
changeset ensures no latitude and/or longitude using those 0/0 are allow
as legal values causing the `EXIFR::TIFF#gps` method to return `nil`.

Does not raise error when it has invalid thumbails data (#65)

Signed-off-by: Remco van 't Veer <remco@remworks.net>
Get rid of some gem warnings

Drop CircleCI

Spend too much time on this before to run tests on multiple rubies, now
it broke again, giving up..

Upgrade rake dev dependency

For CVE-2020-8130 warning on GH.

Migrate CI to CircleCI 2.0

Also note test predicate `refute` isn't supported by older rubies.

Add metadata for RubyGems

This adds direct links to the changelog/bugs. It also allows easier automation of gem updates.
